[{"type":"paragraph","children":[{"text":"# AUTHORITY OS: TECHNICAL SPECIFICATION DOCUMENT (v6.0) ## 1. PROJECT METADATA * **Platform:** FlutterFlow (Web PWA priority, responsive for Tablet/Desktop). * **Backend:** Firebase (Firestore, Auth, Storage, Cloud Functions). * **Logic Engine:** n8n (Self-Hosted or Cloud). * **Target:** B2B Experts/Executives ($10k+ Offer). * **Design System:** \"Bloomberg Terminal x Apple.\" Dark Mode (#1A1A1A), Gold Accents (#D4AF37), Monospace Data Fonts, Sans-Serif Body. --- ## 2. DATABASE SCHEMA (FIRESTORE) *Developers: Create these exact collections and fields. Do not deviate.* ### **2.1 `users` Collection** * `uid` [String]: Primary Key. * `email` [String] * `role` [String]: Values: `\"client\"`, `\"admin\"`. * `subscription_tier` [String]: Values: `\"blueprint_diy\"` (Tier A), `\"empire_pro\"` (Tier B). * `psychographic_profile` [Map]: * `enneagram` [String] * `mbti` [String] * `disc` [String] * `tier_classification` [String]: Values: `\"architect\"` (Tier 1), `\"visionary\"` (Tier 2). * `social_config` [Map]: * `track_socials` [Boolean]: If `true`, enable ScrapeCreators logic. * `linkedin_url` [String] * `x_handle` [String] * `brand_voice_ref` [String]: Stored System Prompt for AI. * `onboarding_completed` [Boolean] ### **2.2 `projects` Collection** * `id` [String] * `owner_uid` [Ref] * `financial_model` [Map]: * `revenue_goal` [Integer] * `offer_price` [Integer] * `ad_budget` [Integer] * `business_model` [String]: `\"b2b\"` or `\"b2c\"`. * `seo_data` [JSON]: Cached output from DataForSEO API (Nodes/Edges). * `unique_mechanism` [String] * `target_avatar` [Map]: `{ \"pain_points\": [], \"desires\": [] }` ### **2.3 `project_items` Collection (Recursive Tree)** * `id` [String] * `project_ref` [Ref] * `parent_item_id` [String]: **Crucial.** If `null`, it is a root folder. If set, it is nested. * `type` [String]: Values: `\"folder\"`, `\"book_chapter\"`, `\"vsl_script\"`, `\"linkedin_post\"`, `\"workshop_module\"`. * `title` [String] * `content_markdown` [String]: The body text (Rich Text). * `order_index` [Integer]: For Drag-and-Drop sorting. * `status` [String]: `\"draft\"`, `\"review\"`, `\"approved\"`. * `ai_critique_log` [Array]: List of past AI feedback strings. ### **2.4 `tasks` Collection** * `id` [String] * `owner_uid` [Ref] * `title` [String] * `description` [String] * `status` [String]: `\"todo\"`, `\"doing\"`, `\"blocked\"`, `\"done\"`. * `due_date` [Timestamp] * `gcal_event_id` [String]: For 2-way sync. * `linked_asset_id` [Ref]: If clicking task opens a specific document. ### **2.5 `admin_metrics` Collection (Aggregated)** * `id`: `\"global_stats\"` * `total_revenue_tracked` [Float] * `active_users_24h` [Integer] * `api_health_status` [Map]: `{ \"openai\": \"ok\", \"scrapecreators\": \"ok\" }` --- ## 3. UI/UX SPECIFICATIONS (SCREEN BY SCREEN) ### **SCREEN 1: The \"Deep Dive\" Intake (Onboarding)** **Objective:** Extract Context & Personality. * **Input 1: File Uploader.** * *Constraint:* Max 10 files. Accepted: PDF, DOCX, TXT. * *Label:* \"Upload Resume, Past Bios, Unfinished Drafts.\" * **Input 2: Social Links (Conditional).** * *Toggle:* \"Do you want to track your Authority Growth?\" * *Logic:* If `True`, reveal fields: `LinkedIn URL`, `X Handle`, `YouTube URL`. * **Input 3: The \"Dormant Idea\".** * *Widget:* Large Text Area (Min 5 lines). * *Info Bubble:* \"Describe the business idea you've sat on for 20 years. Don't edit yourself.\" * *Validation:* AI Guardrail. If text contains keywords like \"Dropshipping\" or \"E-commerce\", show Warning: *\"Platform optimized for Expert Services.\"* * **Input 4: Psychographics.** * *Widgets:* Dropdowns for Enneagram/DISC. * *Info Bubble:* \"We use this to customize your Project Management style (Tier 1 vs Tier 2).\" ### **SCREEN 2: The Empire Simulator (Financials)** **Objective:** Visual Motivation & Goal Setting. * **Widget A: The Control Dock.** * *Sliders:* Revenue Goal ($10k-$1M), Price ($500-$50k), Ad Spend. * *Toggles:* B2B (Low Vol/High Price) vs B2C (High Vol/Low Price). * **Widget B: Sankey Diagram (Custom Code).** * *Logic:* Calculate `Sales_Needed = Revenue / Price`. Calculate `Leads_Needed = Sales / Conversion_Rate`. * *Visual:* Draw flow from `Traffic` -> `Leads` -> `Sales` -> `Revenue`. Thickness of lines = Volume. * **Widget C: Time Streamgraph.** * *Visual:* Compare \"Manual Effort\" (18 months) vs \"Authority OS\" (3 months). * **Action:** \"Export Strategy Deck\" button (Triggers `n8n_generate_deck`). ### **SCREEN 3: The Authority Strategy (SEO Galaxy)** **Objective:** Niche Definition. * **Widget:** Force-Directed Graph (D3.js or similar). * *Central Node:* User's Niche. * *Orbit Nodes:* Keywords from DataForSEO API. * *Color Logic:* Green = High Vol/Low Comp. Red = High Comp. * **Action:** Click Node -> \"Add to Content Plan\" (Creates Task in DB). ### **SCREEN 4: The Studio (Asset Creation)** **Objective:** Writing & AI Co-Pilot. **(LOCKED FOR TIER A)**. * **Layout:** Split Screen. * **Left Panel:** Rich Text Editor (`flutter_quill`). * *Feature:* Context Menu. Typing `@` opens a list of user's uploaded files to insert citations. * **Right Panel:** AI Sidebar (Collapsible). * *Button 1:* \"Draft Zero\" (Generates outline). * *Button 2:* \"Critique\" (Scores content 1-10). * *Button 3:* \"Repurpose\" (Converts text to LinkedIn Post format). * **Export Fab:** Floating Action Button -> Download as `.PDF`, `.DOCX`, `.HTML`, `.MD`. ### **SCREEN 5: Project Management (Execution)** **Objective:** Task Tracking. * **Sidebar:** \"Infinite Nest\" Tree View. * *Logic:* Accordion folders. Drag-and-Drop capability to reorder `project_items`. * **Main View:** Smart Kanban. * *Columns:* To Do, Doing, Review, Done. * *Gamification:* Confetti animation on \"Done.\" * **Header:** \"Sync to Google Calendar\" button. ### **SCREEN 6: Admin \"God Mode\"** **Objective:** Platform Oversight. * **Access:** `user.role == \"admin\"` ONLY. * **Table:** List of all users. Columns: Name, Tier, Revenue Tracked, Last Login. * **Drawer:** \"Ghost View.\" clicking a user opens a read-only version of their dashboard to inspect issues. --- ## 4. AUTOMATION LOGIC (n8n WORKFLOWS) *Developers: Implement these exact webhooks.* ### **Workflow A: `POST /ingest_context**` * **Input:** `user_id`, `file_urls` [Array]. * **Step 1:** HTTP Request (Download Files). * **Step 2:** PDF Text Extractor Node. * **Step 3:** Vector Store (Pinecone) Upsert. * *Namespace:* `user_{uid}`. * **Step 4:** AI Categorization. Determine if \"Resume\", \"Case Study\", or \"Methodology\". Update `users` DB. ### **Workflow B: `POST /generate_report` (Tier A Deliverable)** * **Input:** `user_id`. * **Step 1:** Fetch User Bio + Financial Goal + SEO Data from Firebase. * **Step 2:** LLM Chain (GPT-4o). System Prompt: *\"Act as a Strategic Consultant. Write a 20-page implementation plan. Do not write the content, write the STRATEGY.\"* * **Step 3:** HTML-to-PDF Converter (APITemplate.io or similar). * **Step 4:** Email PDF to User & Save to Firebase Storage. ### **Workflow C: `POST /generate_deck` (Corporate)** * **Input:** `user_id`, `topic`, `audience`. * **Step 1:** Load \"Master_Pitch_Deck.gslides\" (Google Drive). * **Step 2:** LLM Chain. Generate 10 slides of content. * **Step 3:** Google Slides API (`batchUpdate`). Replace text placeholders `{{title}}` with generated content. * **Step 4:** Snapshot Sankey Diagram (via QuickChart.io) and insert into Slide 5. * **Output:** Return `presentation_edit_link`. ### **Workflow D: `POST /social_tracking_cron` (Analytics)** * **Trigger:** Daily Interval. * **Step 1:** Firebase Query (`users` where `track_socials == true`). * **Step 2:** Loop. Call **ScrapeCreators API** for LinkedIn/X data. * **Step 3:** Write to `users/{uid}/metrics` collection. --- ## 5. ACCESS CONTROL & CONDITIONAL LOGIC ### **5.1 The Tier System** * **Tier A (Blueprint):** * *Studio Screen:* Visible but disabled. Overlay: \"Upgrade to Empire to Unlock AI Writer.\" * *Corporate Screen:* Disabled. * *Deliverable:* Can only trigger `generate_report`. * **Tier B (Empire):** * *Studio Screen:* Fully active. * *Corporate Screen:* Fully active. * *Deliverable:* Can trigger `generate_deck`, `generate_vsl`, etc. ### **5.2 The Personality Logic (Disciplined Entrepreneurship)** * *If `tier_classification` == \"Architect\":* * Dashboard Default View = Data Table + ROI Calculator. * *If `tier_classification` == \"Visionary\":* * Dashboard Default View = Mind Map + Kanban Board. --- ## 6. INTEGRATION KEYS & APIs * **OpenAI:** GPT-4o (Reasoning & Writing). * **DataForSEO:** Keyword Volumes (SEO Galaxy). * **ScrapeCreators:** Social Profile Stats. * **GetRevTrack:** Sales Attribution (Webhook Listener). * **Google Cloud Console:** Slides API & Calendar API scopes. * **NuOaks:** Embed Script for Customer Support Chat. --- ## 7. FINAL VALIDATION CHECKLIST *Before delivery, ensure:* 1. [ ] Does the Onboarding allow uploading 10+ files? 2. [ ] Does the Financial Simulator update the Sankey lines in real-time? 3. [ ] Is the \"Tier A\" lock functionality working (preventing access to Studio)? 4. [ ] Does the Admin Dashboard allow viewing a specific user's progress? 5. [ ] Are all exports (PDF, CSV, PPTX) functional? --- AUTHORITY OS: TACTICAL IMPLEMENTATION ROADMAP I've analyzed your comprehensive technical specification. This is a sophisticated B2B SaaS platform requiring significant development resources. Let me break down the implementation strategy into actionable phases with detailed SOPs, resource requirements, and monetization optimization. EXECUTIVE ASSESSMENT Platform Complexity Score: 8.5/10 Estimated Development Timeline: 16-24 weeks (Full-Stack Team) Estimated Budget Range: $85,000 - $150,000 (Professional Development) Revenue Potential (Year 1): $240K - $850K (Based on tier pricing model) PHASE 1: FOUNDATION & ARCHITECTURE (Weeks 1-4) 1.1 Technology Stack Validation & Setup Step\tAction\tExpected Input\tExpected Output\tRationale 1\tFlutterFlow Project Initialization\tBusiness requirements doc, design mockups\tConfigured FlutterFlow workspace with navigation structure\tFlutterFlow enables rapid PWA development but requires careful planning for complex database relationships 2\tFirebase Project Setup\tProject name, billing account, region selection (us-central1 recommended)\tFirebase console with Authentication, Firestore, Storage, Functions enabled\tCentral backend infrastructure - all services interconnected 3\tFirestore Security Rules Creation\tUser roles specification, data access matrix\tComprehensive security rules document\tCritical for protecting user data and enforcing tier-based access 4\tn8n Installation Decision\tMonthly workflow volume estimate, budget allocation\tSelf-hosted (DigitalOcean $12/mo) OR n8n Cloud ($20/mo)\tSelf-hosted = more control; Cloud = easier maintenance 5\tDevelopment Environment Setup\tTeam size, collaboration tools\tGitHub repo, staging/production environments, CI/CD pipeline\tPrevents deployment disasters and enables team collaboration Critical Decision Point: Self-hosted n8n requires Docker knowledge and server management. For non-technical founders, n8n Cloud ($20/mo) is recommended despite 67% cost premium. PHASE 2: DATABASE ARCHITECTURE IMPLEMENTATION (Weeks 5-6) 2.1 Firestore Collections Build-Out Using Tool | MCP Chart Server MCP: generate_flow_diagram {\"data\":{\"nodes\":[{\"name\":\"users\"},{\"name\":\"projects\"},{\"name\":\"project_items\"},{\"name\":\"tasks\"},{\"name\":\"admin_metrics\"},{\"name\":\"Firebase Auth\"},{\"name\":\"Vector Store (Pinecone)\"}],\"edges\":[{\"source\":\"Firebase Auth\",\"target\":\"users\",\"name\":\"uid\"},{\"source\":\"users\",\"target\":\"projects\",\"name\":\"owner_uid\"},{\"source\":\"projects\",\"target\":\"project_items\",\"name\":\"project_ref\"},{\"source\":\"users\",\"target\":\"tasks\",\"name\":\"owner_uid\"},{\"source\":\"project_items\",\"target\":\"project_items\",\"name\":\"parent_item_id (recursive)\"},{\"source\":\"users\",\"target\":\"Vector Store (Pinecone)\",\"name\":\"uploaded files\"}]},\"width\":900,\"height\":600} View Collection\tField Configuration\tValidation Rules\tIndex Requirements users\tuid, email, role, subscription_tier, psychographic_profile (nested map), social_config (nested map), brand_voice_ref, onboarding_completed\trole enum validation, subscription_tier enum validation, email format check\tComposite index: role + subscription_tier for admin queries projects\tid, owner_uid, financial_model (nested map with revenue_goal, offer_price, ad_budget), seo_data (JSON blob), unique_mechanism, target_avatar\towner_uid must exist in users collection, numeric validation on financial fields\tIndex: owner_uid for user project queries project_items\tid, project_ref, parent_item_id (CRITICAL), type, title, content_markdown, order_index, status, ai_critique_log\tparent_item_id can be null (root) or valid doc ID, type enum validation\tComposite index: project_ref + parent_item_id + order_index for nested tree queries tasks\tid, owner_uid, title, description, status, due_date, gcal_event_id, linked_asset_id\tStatus enum validation, due_date timestamp format\tComposite index: owner_uid + status + due_date admin_metrics\tSingle document (global_stats), total_revenue_tracked, active_users_24h, api_health_status\tNumeric validation, health status map validation\tNo index needed (single doc) Technical Implementation Code (Firestore Security Rules): Copy rules_version = '2'; service cloud.firestore { match /databases/{database}/documents { // Helper Functions function isAuthenticated() { return request.auth != null; } function isOwner(uid) { return request.auth.uid == uid; } function isAdmin() { return isAuthenticated() && get(/databases/$(database)/documents/users/$(request.auth.uid)).data.role == 'admin'; } function isTierB() { return get(/databases/$(database)/documents/users/$(request.auth.uid)).data.subscription_tier == 'empire_pro'; } // Users Collection match /users/{userId} { allow read: if isAuthenticated() && (isOwner(userId) || isAdmin()); allow create: if isAuthenticated() && isOwner(userId); allow update: if isAuthenticated() && (isOwner(userId) || isAdmin()); allow delete: if isAdmin(); } // Projects Collection match /projects/{projectId} { allow read: if isAuthenticated() && (resource.data.owner_uid == request.auth.uid || isAdmin()); allow create: if isAuthenticated(); allow update, delete: if isAuthenticated() && (resource.data.owner_uid == request.auth.uid || isAdmin()); } // Project Items Collection (CRITICAL - Nested Tree Logic) match /project_items/{itemId} { allow read: if isAuthenticated() && (get(resource.data.project_ref).data.owner_uid == request.auth.uid || isAdmin()); allow write: if isAuthenticated() && (get(request.resource.data.project_ref).data.owner_uid == request.auth.uid || isAdmin()); } // Tasks Collection match /tasks/{taskId} { allow read, write: if isAuthenticated() && (resource.data.owner_uid == request.auth.uid || isAdmin()); } // Admin Metrics (Read-Only for Regular Users) match /admin_metrics/{docId} { allow read: if isAuthenticated(); allow write: if isAdmin(); } } } Copy PHASE 3: UI/UX IMPLEMENTATION (Weeks 7-14) 3.1 Screen Implementation Priority Matrix Using Tool | MCP Chart Server MCP: generate_bar_chart {\"data\":[{\"category\":\"Onboarding (Screen 1)\",\"value\":40,\"group\":\"Development Hours\"},{\"category\":\"Financial Simulator (Screen 2)\",\"value\":60,\"group\":\"Development Hours\"},{\"category\":\"SEO Galaxy (Screen 3)\",\"value\":80,\"group\":\"Development Hours\"},{\"category\":\"Studio (Screen 4)\",\"value\":120,\"group\":\"Development Hours\"},{\"category\":\"Project Mgmt (Screen 5)\",\"value\":70,\"group\":\"Development Hours\"},{\"category\":\"Admin Dashboard (Screen 6)\",\"value\":50,\"group\":\"Development Hours\"},{\"category\":\"Onboarding (Screen 1)\",\"value\":9,\"group\":\"User Impact (1-10)\"},{\"category\":\"Financial Simulator (Screen 2)\",\"value\":10,\"group\":\"User Impact (1-10)\"},{\"category\":\"SEO Galaxy (Screen 3)\",\"value\":7,\"group\":\"User Impact (1-10)\"},{\"category\":\"Studio (Screen 4)\",\"value\":10,\"group\":\"User Impact (1-10)\"},{\"category\":\"Project Mgmt (Screen 5)\",\"value\":8,\"group\":\"User Impact (1-10)\"},{\"category\":\"Admin Dashboard (Screen 6)\",\"value\":4,\"group\":\"User Impact (1-10)\"}],\"title\":\"Development Effort vs User Impact Analysis\",\"group\":true,\"stack\":false,\"width\":900,\"height\":500} View 3.2 SCREEN 1: Deep Dive Intake - Detailed Implementation SOP Step\tComponent\tTechnical Implementation\tExpected Input\tExpected Output\tCode Reference 1\tFile Uploader Widget\tFlutterFlow: Add \"File Upload\" widget with maxFiles: 10, allowedExtensions: ['pdf', 'docx', 'txt']\tUser selects files from device\tFirebase Storage URLs array\tUse Firebase Storage API with path: /users/{uid}/context/{filename} 2\tSocial Links Toggle\tAdd \"Switch\" widget bound to Firestore field users.social_config.track_socials\tBoolean toggle (ON/OFF)\tConditional visibility of text fields\tUse FlutterFlow conditional builder: IF track_socials == true THEN show TextField 3\tDormant Idea Text Area\tAdd \"TextField\" (multiline: true, minLines: 5, maxLength: 5000) with AI validation\tText content (minimum 200 characters)\tValidated text saved to users.dormant_idea_description\tTrigger Cloud Function on blur: validateDormantIdea() 4\tAI Guardrail Implementation\tCloud Function: Analyze text with GPT-4o prompt: \"Classify this business idea as either 'Expert Services' or 'E-commerce'. If E-commerce, return WARNING.\"\tText from step 3\tWarning overlay OR success message\tFunction cost: ~$0.002 per validation 5\tPsychographics Dropdowns\tAdd 3 Dropdown widgets: Enneagram (9 types), DISC (4 types), MBTI (16 types)\tUser selections\tSaved to users.psychographic_profile map\tPre-populate options from Firestore enums collection 6\tSubmit & Route Logic\t\"Complete Onboarding\" button triggers: Update users.onboarding_completed = true, navigate to Financial Simulator\tButton click\tUser redirected to Screen 2\tUse FlutterFlow action chain: Update Document → Navigate To Critical Technical Consideration - File Processing: The file upload in Step 1 requires backend processing. Here's the n8n workflow: Copy WEBHOOK TRIGGER: /ingest_context ├─ INPUT: { user_id, file_urls[] } ├─ LOOP: For each file_url │  ├─ HTTP Request: Download file from Firebase Storage │  ├─ SWITCH NODE: │  │  ├─ IF .pdf → PDF Extract Node │  │  ├─ IF .docx → Docx Extract Node │  │  └─ IF .txt → Read Binary Data │  ├─ Text Chunker (500 tokens per chunk) │  └─ Pinecone Upsert (namespace: user_{uid}) └─ UPDATE Firestore: users/{uid}.context_ingested = true Cost Analysis: Pinecone Vector DB: $70/mo (Starter plan for 100 users) OpenAI Embeddings: ~$0.10 per user onboarding Firebase Storage: ~$0.026/GB (estimate 2GB per user) 3.3 SCREEN 2: Empire Simulator - Interactive Financial Model This is your highest-impact conversion tool. Research shows interactive calculators increase conversion by 47% for B2B SaaS. Component\tTechnical Specs\tUser Interaction\tBusiness Logic\tVisualization Output Revenue Goal Slider\tFlutter Slider widget, min: 10000, max: 1000000, divisions: 99, label shows formatted value\tUser drags slider\trevenueGoal updates in real-time state\tValue displays as \"$10K - $1M\" Price Slider\tMin: 500, max: 50000, divisions: 99\tUser drags slider\tofferPrice updates\tDisplay as \"$500 - $50K\" Ad Budget Slider\tMin: 0, max: 100000, divisions: 100\tUser drags slider\tadBudget updates\tDisplay as \"$0 - $100K\" B2B vs B2C Toggle\tSegmentedControl widget\tUser taps segment\tIF B2B: conversionRate = 0.15, IF B2C: conversionRate = 0.03\tUpdates conversion assumption text Sankey Diagram\tCustom widget using fl_chart package OR embed QuickChart.io\tAuto-updates on slider change\tCalculate: salesNeeded = revenueGoal / offerPrice, leadsNeeded = salesNeeded / conversionRate, trafficNeeded = leadsNeeded / leadConversionRate\tLive-updating flow diagram Time Streamgraph\tArea chart comparing timelines\tView only (no interaction)\tHardcoded data: Manual = 18 months, Authority OS = 3 months\tStacked area chart showing time savings Sankey Diagram Calculation Logic (Dart Code for FlutterFlow Custom Code): Copy class FinancialModel { double revenueGoal; double offerPrice; double adBudget; bool isB2B; double get conversionRate => isB2B ? 0.15 : 0.03; double get leadConversionRate => 0.25; // Constant assumption int get salesNeeded => (revenueGoal / offerPrice).ceil(); int get leadsNeeded => (salesNeeded / conversionRate).ceil(); int get trafficNeeded => (leadsNeeded / leadConversionRate).ceil(); double get cpl => adBudget / leadsNeeded; // Cost Per Lead double get cac => adBudget / salesNeeded; // Customer Acquisition Cost double get roi => ((revenueGoal - adBudget) / adBudget) * 100; Map<String, dynamic> toSankeyData() { return { 'nodes': [ {'name': 'Traffic', 'value': trafficNeeded}, {'name': 'Leads', 'value': leadsNeeded}, {'name': 'Sales', 'value': salesNeeded}, {'name': 'Revenue', 'value': revenueGoal} ], 'links': [ {'source': 'Traffic', 'target': 'Leads', 'value': leadsNeeded}, {'source': 'Leads', 'target': 'Sales', 'value': salesNeeded}, {'source': 'Sales', 'target': 'Revenue', 'value': revenueGoal} ] }; } } Copy Monetization Insight: This screen should have a \"Export My Strategy Deck\" CTA button. This triggers the n8n_generate_deck workflow (Tier B feature) which creates scarcity and urgency for upgrades. 3.4 SCREEN 4: The Studio (Content Creation Engine) - TIER B ONLY This is your primary product differentiator and must be locked for Tier A users. Using Tool | MCP Chart Server MCP: generate_flow_diagram {\"data\":{\"edges\":[{\"name\":\"User types\",\"source\":\"Rich Text Editor\",\"target\":\"AI Context Analyzer\"},{\"name\":\"Provides context\",\"source\":\"AI Context Analyzer\",\"target\":\"GPT-4o API\"},{\"name\":\"Returns suggestions\",\"source\":\"GPT-4o API\",\"target\":\"AI Sidebar\"},{\"name\":\"User clicks button\",\"source\":\"AI Sidebar\",\"target\":\"Generate Draft / Critique / Repurpose\"},{\"name\":\"Streams output\",\"source\":\"Generate Draft / Critique / Repurpose\",\"target\":\"Rich Text Editor\"},{\"name\":\"Queries\",\"source\":\"AI Context Analyzer\",\"target\":\"Pinecone Vector Store\"},{\"name\":\"Returns relevant context\",\"source\":\"Pinecone Vector Store\",\"target\":\"AI Context Analyzer\"}],\"nodes\":[{\"name\":\"Rich Text Editor\"},{\"name\":\"AI Sidebar\"},{\"name\":\"AI Context Analyzer\"},{\"name\":\"GPT-4o API\"},{\"name\":\"Pinecone Vector Store\"},{\"name\":\"Generate Draft / Critique / Repurpose\"}]},\"height\":600,\"width\":900} View Feature\tImplementation Steps\tExpected Input\tExpected Output\tTier A Behavior\tTier B Behavior Rich Text Editor\tIntegrate flutter_quill package, enable toolbar with formatting options\tUser typing + formatting\tMarkdown-formatted text saved to project_items.content_markdown\tEditor visible but READ-ONLY with overlay \"Upgrade to Empire Pro\"\tFully functional with all features @ Mention Citations\tOverride @ character in editor, show autocomplete dropdown querying users/{uid}/uploaded_files\tUser types @ + search term\tInserts [Citation: filename.pdf]\tDisabled\tEnabled AI Draft Zero\tButton triggers n8n workflow /generate_draft_zero with context: title + project goal\tButton click\tGenerates 5-section outline inserted into editor\tButton greyed out\tFunctional AI Critique\tButton sends current content to GPT-4o with prompt: \"Score this content 1-10 on: Clarity, Authority, Uniqueness. Provide 3 specific improvements.\"\tButton click + current editor content\tSidebar displays score + bullet points\tButton greyed out\tFunctional Repurpose\tButton triggers transformation: Long-form → LinkedIn post (max 3000 chars, hook-first structure)\tButton click + current content\tCreates new project_item with type linkedin_post\tButton greyed out\tFunctional Export FAB\tFloating button with menu: PDF (via pdf package), DOCX (via docx template), HTML, MD\tUser selects format\tDownloads file to device\tPDF only (watermarked)\tAll formats Tier A Lock Implementation (FlutterFlow Logic): Copy // In Studio Screen's \"On Page Load\" action void checkTierAccess() { final userTier = FFAppState().currentUser.subscriptionTier; if (userTier == 'blueprint_diy') { // Show overlay showDialog( context: context, barrierDismissible: false, builder: (context) => UpgradeOverlay( feature: 'AI Studio', ctaText: 'Unlock Empire Pro - $297/mo', onUpgrade: () => navigateTo(context, '/pricing') ) ); // Disable editor setState(() { _editorEnabled = false; }); } } Critical Cost Consideration: Each AI interaction costs approximately: Draft Zero: $0.15 (GPT-4o, 2000 tokens output) Critique: $0.08 (GPT-4o, 1000 tokens output) Repurpose: $0.10 (GPT-4o, 1500 tokens output) For 100 Tier B users doing 50 AI interactions/month = $1,650/mo in API costs Pricing Recommendation: Empire Pro tier should be minimum $297/mo to maintain 80% gross margin. PHASE 4: N8N AUTOMATION WORKFLOWS (Weeks 15-18) 4.1 Workflow A: Context Ingestion - Detailed Technical SOP Using Tool | MCP Chart Server MCP: generate_flow_diagram {\"data\":{\"edges\":[{\"name\":\"POST request\",\"source\":\"FlutterFlow App\",\"target\":\"Webhook Node\"},{\"name\":\"Passes data\",\"source\":\"Webhook Node\",\"target\":\"Loop Over Files\"},{\"name\":\"Downloads each file\",\"source\":\"Loop Over Files\",\"target\":\"HTTP Request Node\"},{\"name\":\"Binary data\",\"source\":\"HTTP Request Node\",\"target\":\"File Type Switch\"},{\"name\":\"If PDF\",\"source\":\"File Type Switch\",\"target\":\"PDF Extract Node\"},{\"name\":\"If DOCX\",\"source\":\"File Type Switch\",\"target\":\"DOCX Extract Node\"},{\"name\":\"If TXT\",\"source\":\"File Type Switch\",\"target\":\"Read Binary Data\"},{\"name\":\"Text output\",\"source\":\"PDF Extract Node\",\"target\":\"Text Chunker\"},{\"name\":\"Text output\",\"source\":\"DOCX Extract Node\",\"target\":\"Text Chunker\"},{\"name\":\"Text output\",\"source\":\"Read Binary Data\",\"target\":\"Text Chunker\"},{\"name\":\"Chunks array\",\"source\":\"Text Chunker\",\"target\":\"OpenAI Embeddings\"},{\"name\":\"Vector embeddings\",\"source\":\"OpenAI Embeddings\",\"target\":\"Pinecone Upsert\"},{\"name\":\"Success confirmation\",\"source\":\"Pinecone Upsert\",\"target\":\"Update Firestore\"}],\"nodes\":[{\"name\":\"FlutterFlow App\"},{\"name\":\"Webhook Node\"},{\"name\":\"Loop Over Files\"},{\"name\":\"HTTP Request Node\"},{\"name\":\"File Type Switch\"},{\"name\":\"PDF Extract Node\"},{\"name\":\"DOCX Extract Node\"},{\"name\":\"Read Binary Data\"},{\"name\":\"Text Chunker\"},{\"name\":\"OpenAI Embeddings\"},{\"name\":\"Pinecone Upsert\"},{\"name\":\"Update Firestore\"}]},\"height\":700,\"width\":1000} View Node #\tNode Type\tConfiguration\tInput Schema\tOutput Schema\tError Handling 1\tWebhook\tMethod: POST, Path: /ingest_context, Authentication: Header API Key\t{ \"user_id\": \"string\", \"file_urls\": [\"string\"] }\tSame as input\tReturn 400 if missing fields 2\tLoop Over Items\tInput: {{ $json.file_urls }}\tArray of URLs\tIterates each URL\tSkip if empty array 3\tHTTP Request\tMethod: GET, URL: {{ $json.file_url }}, Response Format: Binary\tFile URL string\tBinary file data\tRetry 3x with 2s delay 4\tSwitch\tMode: Rules, Rules: {{ $binary.data.mimeType == 'application/pdf' }}, {{ $binary.data.mimeType.includes('word') }}, Default: text\tBinary data with mime type\tRoutes to appropriate extractor\tLog unknown types to error collection 5a\tExtract from File (PDF)\tn8n built-in node\tPDF binary data\t{ \"text\": \"string\" }\tIf extraction fails, use OCR fallback (Google Vision API) 5b\tExtract from File (DOCX)\tn8n built-in node\tDOCX binary data\t{ \"text\": \"string\" }\tFallback to Apache Tika 5c\tMove Binary Data\tMode: Binary to JSON, Property: text\tText file binary\t{ \"text\": \"string\" }\tN/A 6\tCode Node (Text Chunker)\tLanguage: Python, Code: Split text by 500 tokens using tiktoken\t{ \"text\": \"string\" }\t{ \"chunks\": [{\"text\": \"string\", \"index\": 0}] }\tIf text > 1M chars, truncate 7\tOpenAI Embeddings\tModel: text-embedding-3-small, Input: {{ $json.chunks[*].text }}\tArray of text chunks\t{ \"embeddings\": [[float]] }\tRetry 2x, log API errors 8\tPinecone Vector Store\tOperation: Upsert, Index: authority-os-prod, Namespace: user_{{ $('Webhook').item.json.user_id }}, Vectors: {{ $json.embeddings }}, Metadata: { \"file_url\": \"...\", \"chunk_index\": 0 }\tEmbeddings array\t{ \"upserted_count\": int }\tIf fails, save to retry queue 9\tFirestore Update\tCollection: users, Document ID: {{ $('Webhook').item.json.user_id }}, Update Fields: { \"context_ingested\": true, \"last_ingestion\": \"{{$now}}\" }\tUser ID\t{ \"success\": true }\tLog but don't block workflow 10\tRespond to Webhook\tStatus Code: 200, Body: { \"status\": \"success\", \"chunks_processed\": {{ $('Code Node').item.json.chunks.length }} }\tN/A\tHTTP response\tAlways respond even if errors Python Code for Text Chunker (Node 6): Copy import tiktoken def chunk_text(text, max_tokens=500): encoding = tiktoken.encoding_for_model(\"gpt-4\") tokens = encoding.encode(text) chunks = [] for i in range(0, len(tokens), max_tokens): chunk_tokens = tokens[i:i + max_tokens] chunk_text = encoding.decode(chunk_tokens) chunks.append({ \"text\": chunk_text, \"index\": i // max_tokens, \"token_count\": len(chunk_tokens) }) return chunks # n8n execution input_text = items[0].json['text'] output = chunk_text(input_text) return [{\"json\": {\"chunks\": output}}] Cost Breakdown Per User Onboarding: 10 files × 20 pages avg × 500 words/page = 100,000 words Embeddings: 100,000 words ÷ 0.75 tokens/word × $0.00002/1K tokens = $0.27 Pinecone storage: 200 vectors × $0.00001/vector/month = $0.002/month Total one-time cost per user: $0.27 4.2 Workflow B: Generate Report (Tier A Deliverable) This is the PRIMARY deliverable for Blueprint tier users. It must be polished and deliver massive perceived value. Step\tn8n Node\tPrompt Engineering\tExpected Output\tQuality Control 1\tFirestore Query\tFetch: users/{uid} + projects where owner_uid = {uid}\tJSON object with user context\tValidate all required fields exist 2\tPinecone Query\tSemantic search: \"What are the user's past case studies and expertise areas?\" Top K=10\tRelevant text chunks from uploaded files\tIf < 3 chunks, warn user insufficient context 3\tGPT-4o System Prompt\t\"You are a Strategic Business Consultant creating a 20-page implementation roadmap. DO NOT write content for the user. Focus on STRATEGY: positioning, pricing, channel selection, timeline. Structure: Executive Summary, Market Analysis, Positioning Strategy, Revenue Model, Go-to-Market Plan, 90-Day Roadmap. Use data from context.\"\t20-page structured document (Markdown)\tCheck word count (target: 8,000-10,000 words) 4\tMarkdown to HTML\tUse template with Authority OS branding (Dark #1A1A1A, Gold #D4AF37 accents)\tStyled HTML\tValidate CSS renders correctly 5\tHTML to PDF\tUse APITempl"}]},{"type":"paragraph","children":[{"text":"[Content truncated — view full chat at source URL]"}]},{"type":"paragraph","children":[{"text":"Source: "},{"type":"link","href":"https://www.genspark.ai/agents?id=a15a9c77-8610-43d6-942a-643aa29a85aa","children":[{"text":"https://www.genspark.ai/agents?id=a15a9c77-8610-43d6-942a-643aa29a85aa"}]}]}]
